    <text id="R13770624T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>General Grant writes Union General in Chief Henry Halleck to announce the meeting
                    of Generals Crook and Averell at Staunton in June, 1864.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    HDQRS. ARMIES OF THE UNITED STATES,
                    <name type="recipient">Maj. Gen. H. W. HALLECK,<lb/> Chief of Staff:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-06-11">June 11, 1864. (Received 11 a. m. 12th.)</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>Richmond papers of this morning announce the junction of Crook and Averell with
                    Hunter, at Staunton, on the 8th instant. A portion of their forces are on the
                    Greenville and Middlebrook road. Five hundred cavalry made a demonstration on
                    Waynesborough, and were repulsed by Imboden; on the 9th advanced again, but were
                    driven back, burning up the railroad as they retired.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>U. S. GRANT,<lb/> Lieut.-Gen.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
